00:50:36.194 --> 00:50:43.445
We must first join our Savior on two other mounts, Mount Olivet and Mount Calvary.

00:50:46.469 --> 00:50:52.138
The only way to Mount Tabor is the royal way of the cross.

00:50:54.682 --> 00:51:05.458
And perhaps of all writers in the history of the Church, no one has made this more clear than one of a later age that is in the glorious Middle Ages, that beautiful author

00:51:06.082 --> 00:51:16.173
of the imitation of Christ, this book which we can never have done within our meditation, especially during Lent.

00:51:16.193 --> 00:51:24.482
As he tells us, Jesus always has many who love his heavenly kingdom, but few who bear his cross.

00:51:25.984 --> 00:51:29.207
He has many who desire consolation, but few who care for trial.

00:51:30.609 --> 00:51:35.154
He finds many to share his table, but few to take part in his fasting.

00:51:36.610 --> 00:51:38.532
All desire to be happy with him.

00:51:39.833 --> 00:51:41.675
Few wish to suffer anything for him.

00:51:43.597 --> 00:51:49.563
Many follow him to the breaking of bread, but few to the drinking of the chalice of his passion.

00:51:50.984 --> 00:51:52.206
Many review his miracles.

00:51:53.387 --> 00:51:55.088
Few approach the shame of his cross.

00:51:56.870 --> 00:51:59.112
Many love him as long as they encounter no hardship.

00:52:00.494 --> 00:52:04.658
Many praise and bless him as long as they receive some comfort from him.

00:52:06.274 --> 00:52:14.404
But if Jesus hides himself and leaves them for a while, they fall either into complaints or into deep dejection.

00:52:18.089 --> 00:52:20.332
To many, this saying is hard.

00:52:22.154 --> 00:52:25.879
Deny thyself, take up thy cross, and follow me.

00:52:27.841 --> 00:52:30.004
But it will be much harder to hear that final word.

00:52:31.346 --> 00:52:34.930
Depart from me ye cursed and to everlasting fire.

00:52:37.570 --> 00:52:45.498
Those who hear the word of the cross and willingly follow it need not fear that they will hear of eternal damnation on the day of judgment.

00:52:46.659 --> 00:52:50.683
The sign of the cross will be in the heavens when the Lord comes to judge.

00:52:51.744 --> 00:53:01.693
Then all the servants of the cross who during life made themselves one with the crucified will draw near with great trust to Christ the judge.

00:53:04.156 --> 00:53:06.418
Why then do you fear to take up the cross

00:53:07.138 --> 00:53:09.781
When through it, you can win a kingdom.

00:53:10.301 --> 00:53:25.576
And the cross is salvation, the cross is life, and the cross is protection from enemies, and the cross infusion of heavenly sweetness, and the cross strength of mind, joy of spirit, highest virtue, perfect holiness.

00:53:26.476 --> 00:53:31.381
There is no salvation of soul nor hope in everlasting life, but in the cross.

00:53:32.863 --> 00:53:36.466
Take up your cross, therefore, and follow Jesus.

00:53:38.338 --> 00:53:50.212
Just then during this let us all take up our cross, let us all willingly accompany our Lord and not sleep but wait with Him in the Garden of Olives and follow Him all the way to Calvary.

00:53:52.134 --> 00:54:04.608
That we may taste in this life through grace that partaking of the divine nature which we found on Mount Tabor and thus inherit one day eternal life forever and ever.

00:54:06.170 --> 00:54:06.450
Amen.

00:54:17.154 --> 00:54:21.581
We hope you enjoyed our final sermon for today entitled, The Road to Mount Tabor.

00:54:23.584 --> 00:54:28.211
Thank you for listening to the Station of the Cross presents, Sermons for Everyday Living.

00:54:29.253 --> 00:54:31.897
May these sermons help you grow in your faith journey.

00:54:32.818 --> 00:54:36.344
Please say three Hail Marys for the priests who preached today's sermons.

00:54:37.345 --> 00:54:41.371
We hope you will join us again next time for, Sermons for Everyday Living.

00:54:42.072 --> 00:54:43.154
Have a blessed day.
